description.data:
A limited edition bourbon as rare as King George, himself.

Introducing Remus Repeal Reserve® Series V, the latest edition of the award-winning Remus Repeal Reserve collection.

Comprised of a medley of five bourbons aged since 2005-2008, Series V is carefully crafted to honor the repeal of Prohibition on December 5, 1933.

The 2021 limited edition leads with dried fruit, rich caramel, maple syrup, roasted nuts and leather. The beginning includes rich toffee and vanilla, followed by chocolate, glazed nuts and oak. The finish offers candied fruit, caramel, baking spice and a lingering oaky rye spice.

namePublicShort.data: December 5, 1933. Prohibition was repealed in the United States with the passage of the 21st Amendment to the United States Constitution. To commemorate this milestone, we created Remus Repeal Reserve. This 2017 limited edition bourbon features a buttery toffee and honeyed smoothness that leads to a bold spiciness, finishing with notes of raisin, fig, and toffee. This highly awarded bourbon was received many accolades to include the Chairman’s Trophy and 97 Points from the Ultimate Spirits Challenge. In short, Remus Repeal Reserve is the best we make. Or as George Remus himself might have said, "some damn fine giggle water." Enjoy!

description.data:
GEORGE REMUS DIDN’T NEED THE 21ST AMENDMENT, BUT WE’LL CELEBRATE ANYWAY.
King George never shied away from an excuse to celebrate. And we have plenty of reasons to choose from. We celebrate a man who had the creativity and commitment to become a legendary bootlegger.
We celebrate a bootlegger who risked family, fortune and freedom to craft the era’s finest bourbon. We celebrate a bourbon that defied an amendment. And we celebrate an amendment that defied one that came before it. So whether you’re toasting the man, the bootlegger, the bourbon or the amendment, join us in toasting with Remus Repeal Reserve®, the perfect complement to GEORGE REMUS® Bourbon in your liquor cabinet.

Eight & Sand refers to the eighth (and fastest) notch on a locomotive’s throttle and the sand used on the wheels to prevent slipping. To wish a train crew an “Eight & Sand” is akin to “smooth sailing.”

Eight & Sand celebrates the timeless journey along the American railway with a classic tribute whiskey uniquely crafted by the MGP distillery team in historic Lawrenceburg, Indiana.

description.data:

Made at our historic 170-year-old distillery in Lawrenceburg, IN, our style is high-rye and relies on our expertise in aging and blending whiskies. We pride ourselves on making whiskies that are greater than the sum of their parts

George Remus Straight Bourbon Whiskey is our flagship Bourbon brand. A high rye profile aged over five years. Rye adds a naturally spicy, cinnamon component that contrasts beautifully with the sweetness of corn. Multiple mash bills enhance the complexity of the spirit.
